# ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md is immutable

`ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md` at the repository root is the **authoritative, immutable** source of architecture rules. It is the ruler against which every refactor, module, and prompt is measured.

## Hard rules

- **NEVER modify `ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md`** under any circumstance — no edits, no reformatting, no fixups, no "small clarifications".
- **NEVER delete or rename** this file.
- **NEVER stage `ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md` for commit.** If `git status` shows it as modified, restore it: `git checkout -- ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md`.
- The four companion documents (`Imperecta_Architecture.md`, `Imperecta_Backend.md`, `Imperecta_Database.md`, `Imperecta_Frontend.md`) **describe** the implementation; `ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md` **prescribes** the rules. Update the four; never the principles.

## When the user asks to amend principles

Treat any request to "fix", "update", "rephrase", or "extend" `ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md` as a policy change. **Stop and ask explicitly**:

> Файл `ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md` помечен как иммутабельный. Подтверди, что хочешь изменить именно его (а не один из четырёх описательных документов), и сформулируй точную правку.

Only after explicit, unambiguous confirmation in the same session may the file be touched. Default action is **refuse and ask**.

## When refactoring conflicts with the document

Per the document itself (Section 0): "When a proposed design conflicts with this document, the design is wrong, not the document — unless the document is explicitly amended first." Bring the conflict to the user; do not silently bend the document.

## Reading allowed, writing forbidden

You may read `ARCHITECTURE_PRINCIPLES.md` freely to ground decisions, generate code, or explain trade-offs. You may quote it. You may not write to it.
